    The world's most detailed globe
  






Climb the tallest mountains.
Discover cities around the world.

keyboard_arrow_down




 


 








Create stories and maps


With creation tools, you can draw on the map, add your photos and videos, customize your view, and share and collaborate with others.






















Create on Earth






Draw on the map


Add placemarks to highlight key locations in your project, or draw lines and shapes directly on the map.














Add your photos and videos


Feature images and videos on your map to add rich contextual information.














Customize your view


Make use of Google Earth's detailed globe by tilting the map to save a perfect 3D view or diving into Street View for a 360 experience.














Share your story with the world


Collaborate with others like a Google Doc and share your story as a presentation.





















          Adding placemarks and lines to Google Earth.

    Find someplace you love
  


        Explore worldwide satellite imagery and 3D buildings and terrain for hundreds of cities. Zoom to your house or anywhere else, then dive in for a 360° perspective with Street View.
















    Choose your adventure with Voyager
  


        Take a guided tour around the globe with some of the world's leading storytellers, scientists, and nonprofits. Immerse yourself in new cultures and test your knowledge of the world.






















    Catch Carmen Sandiego

               Google Earth on web


 


        Now available on Chrome and coming soon to more browsers.



















 







               Google Earth on mobile


 


        Explore the globe with a swipe of your finger. Available on Android and iOS.



















 







               Google Earth Pro on desktop


 


        Create maps with advanced tools on PC, Mac, or Linux.






























    Tell your story with Google Earth
  


        Meet three people who are using Google Earth to protect rivers, inspire students, and revisit their birth country.






        Play
      



















    Google Earth in Action
  


        The India Literacy Project teamed up with Google Earth to take children around India on virtual field trips and learn about their world.






        Play
      



















    Behind the Scenes of 3D Imagery
  


        Google Earth is the most photorealistic, digital version of our planet. Where do the images come from?  How are they they put together? And how often are they updated? In this video, learn about the pixels, planes, and people that create Google Earth’s 3D imagery.






        Play
      



















    Geo for Good
  


        In 2018, nonprofit mapping and technology specialists gathered in California to learn about Google's mapping tools and share a passion for planetary change.

Try Earth Studio




 
















Let the world tell your story


Earth Studio is an animation tool for Google&nbspEarth’s satellite and 3D imagery.




play_circle_filled




keyboard_arrow_down




















Inside Earth Studio



      Powerful motion design, all in the browser. Earth Studio gives you the tools you need to create professional content with Google&nbspEarth imagery.
      



      Read more in the 
Documentation
.
    


















Keyframe Animation


Earth Studio uses keyframes, just like other industry-standard animation tools. Move the globe, set a keyframe, rinse and repeat. It’s that easy.














Quick-Start Projects


Create an orbit, or fly from point to point. Select from up to five templates to get started - no animation experience needed.














Animatable Effects


Animate custom attributes such as the sun's position, the camera's field of view and more.














3D Camera Export


Easily add map labels and pins in post production. Earth Studio supports camera export to Adobe After Effects.












































Read more in the 
Documentation
.








Try the Earth Studio preview


Earth Studio is free to use and works with the desktop version of Google&nbspChrome. Sign in with your Google account to request access.

Plan Now Merchant Center Google Merchant Center lets you manage how your in-store and online product inventory appears on Google. This helps get your products in front of the hundreds of millions of people who do shopping related searches on Google each day. Create your account Sign in Here’s what you can do with Merchant Center Show your most accurate store and product information Ensure potential customers can find the details that matter when they search on Google, like your product prices and in-store availability. Reach shoppers across Google’s entire suite of sites and networks Get more sales by showing your products to relevant customers across paid and unpaid channels. Discover more insights Get actionable reporting on pricing, merchandising, and more to drive your business strategy. Tell us your goal and we'll find you the tools to reach it I want to: Increase awareness Increase awareness Acquire new customers Drive online sales Grow local sales Drive app installs App campaigns App campaigns Connect with new and existing app customers by promoting your app across Google's suite of sites and networks, including Google Play. Learn more Discovery ads Discovery ads Reach up to 3 billion people with visually inspiring creative as they scroll through Google's most popular feeds, including: YouTube Home and Watch Next, Discover, and the Gmail Social and Promotions tabs. Learn more Display campaigns Display campaigns Promote your brand to new customers using Display campaigns with the ability to choose your audiences ("custom audiences"), showing visually engaging ads across millions of websites and apps. Learn more Video campaigns Video campaigns Whether you’re an established company or an up-and-coming business, YouTube increases awareness of your brand through efficient reach formats, highly relevant content and engaging creative. Learn more Free local product listings Free local product listings List your in-store products for free to reach nearby shoppers who are searching across Google, including the Shopping tab, Google Search and Google Images. Learn more Google My Business Google My Business Manage how your business information appears to customers looking for your stores on Google Search and Maps. Learn more Local campaigns Local campaigns Promote your physical stores across Search, Maps, YouTube and Display with one simple cross-channel campaign designed to drive in-person visits to your locations. Learn more Local inventory ads Local inventory ads Showcase your in-store product availability to nearby shoppers to bring them to your store. Learn more Smart Bidding with store visits Smart Bidding with store visits Optimize your Search and Shopping campaigns for total omnichannel return on ad spend. Advanced machine learning adjusts bids for each and every user search to drive both online and in-store sales. Learn more Smart Shopping campaigns Smart Shopping campaigns Drive in-store sales by adding a ‘store visits’ goal to your Smart Shopping campaigns , which show your products to shoppers searching across Google. Learn more Merchant Center Merchant Center Add your products and manage how your online and offline inventory shows across Google's paid and unpaid channels. Learn more Display campaigns Display campaigns Find new customers with Smart Display campaigns, which show visually engaging ads across millions of websites and apps. Optimize performance of the campaigns with target CPA bidding. Learn more Search campaigns Search campaigns Connect with new customers on Google Search by using call ads and complementing your responsive search ads. Learn more Smart Shopping campaigns Smart Shopping campaigns Acquire new customers by selecting 'new customer acquisition' as your goal in your Smart Shopping campaigns, which show your products to shoppers searching across Google. Learn more Video campaigns Video campaigns Use the power of video to acquire new customers and drive sales on one of Google's most engaging platforms — YouTube . Learn more Buy on Google Buy on Google Sell your products directly on Google with zero Google commission fees. Use your existing payment provider to get started. Learn more Shopping campaigns with partners Shopping campaigns with partners Collaborate with your brand manufacturer partners - via shared campaigns and budgets - to boost sales for specific products across Google. Learn more Display campaigns Display campaigns Drive online sales using Display campaigns to show new and existing customers visually engaging ads across millions of websites and apps. Select Smart Display campaigns to automatically optimize to your target return and ad spend. Learn more Free product listings Free product listings List your products for free to reach searching shoppers across Google, including the Shopping tab, Google Search and Google Images. Learn more Manufacturer Center Manufacturer Center If you’re a brand manufacturer, you can control how your products appear across Google by uploading the most up-to-date and authoritative info and imagery to Manufacturer Center. Learn more Search campaigns Search campaigns Drive online sales with potential customers on Google Search by using responsive search ads. Learn more Smart Shopping campaigns Smart Shopping campaigns Grow online sales by promoting your products to searching shoppers across Google. On average, advertisers using Smart Shopping campaigns see 20% higher conversion value compared to Standard Shopping campaigns. Learn more Video campaigns Video campaigns Use the power of video to acquire new customers, boost web traffic and drive new sales on one of Google's most engaging platforms — YouTube. Learn more View more partners Try out these tools to push your online presence further Promotions Highlight your promotions on Shopping campaigns and unpaid listings to push shoppers to make the purchase with you. Customer reviews Collect reviews from your customers and earn a seller rating badge to display on your website. Product Ratings Add a 5-star rating and review system to your listings and ads to help shoppers feel more confident in your products.     <section class="intro-modal">
    <div class="close-autoplay-holder">
      <button class="autoplay animation" ng-class="{'no-animation': stepsCtrl.autoplayActive}"
          ng-if="stepsCtrl.autoplayEnabled" ng-click="stepsCtrl.toggleAutoplay()" ng-disabled="stepsCtrl.activeStep == 4">
        <svg ng-if="stepsCtrl.autoplayActive" aria-hidden="true" role="img">
          <use xlink:href="#pause"></use>
        </svg>
        <svg ng-if="!stepsCtrl.autoplayActive" aria-hidden="true" role="img">
          <use xlink:href="#play"></use>
        </svg>
      </button>
      <button class="modal-close" tabindex="0" ng-click="stepsCtrl.closeModal()"
          aria-label="{[stepsCtrl.introGlobalMeta.close_modal.translatableMeta.text]}">
        <svg aria-hidden="true" role="img">
          <use xlink:href="#close"></use>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>

    <section class="intro-modal">
    <div class="close-autoplay-holder">
      <button class="autoplay animation" ng-class="{'no-animation': stepsCtrl.autoplayActive}"
          ng-if="stepsCtrl.autoplayEnabled" ng-click="stepsCtrl.toggleAutoplay()" ng-disabled="stepsCtrl.activeStep == 4">
        <svg ng-if="stepsCtrl.autoplayActive" aria-hidden="true" role="img">
          <use xlink:href="#pause"></use>
        </svg>
        <svg ng-if="!stepsCtrl.autoplayActive" aria-hidden="true" role="img">
          <use xlink:href="#play"></use>
        </svg>
      </button>
      <button class="modal-close" tabindex="0" ng-click="stepsCtrl.closeModal()"
          aria-label="{[stepsCtrl.introGlobalMeta.close_modal.translatableMeta.text]}">
        <svg aria-hidden="true" role="img">
          <use xlink:href="#close"></use>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
      <ol class="modal-hidden" tabindex="0" aria-label="Learn how Google Ads works">
    <li>
      <h2>{[stepsCtrl.content[0].headline]}</h2>
      <h3>{[stepsCtrl.content[0].title]}</h3>
      <ol aria-label="{[stepsCtrl.content[0].title]}">
        <li>
          <h4>{[stepsCtrl.content[0].cards[0].title]}</h4>
          <p>{[stepsCtrl.content[0].cards[0].text]}</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>{[stepsCtrl.content[0].cards[1].title]}</h4>
          <p>{[stepsCtrl.content[0].cards[1].text]}</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>{[stepsCtrl.content[0].cards[2].title]}</h4>
          <p>{[stepsCtrl.content[0].cards[2].text]}</p>
        </li>
        <li ng-bind-html="stepsCtrl.content[0].experienced_advertiser_text">
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>{[stepsCtrl.content[1].headline]}</h2>
      <h3>{[stepsCtrl.content[1].title]}</h3>
      <ol>
        <li ng-repeat="tile in stepsCtrl.content[1].tiles">
          <h4>{[tile.title]}</h4>
          <p>{[tile.text]}</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>{[stepsCtrl.content[2].headline]}</h3>
      <h2>{[stepsCtrl.content[2].title]}</h2>
      <ol>
        <li ng-repeat="accordeon in stepsCtrl.content[2].accordeons">
          <h4>{[accordeon.title]}</h4>
          <p>{[accordeon.text]}</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>{[stepsCtrl.content[3].title]}</h2>
      <h3>{[stepsCtrl.content[3].text]}</h3>
      <a href="{[stepsCtrl.content[3].button_link]}">{[stepsCtrl.content[3].button_text]}</a>
      <p>{[stepsCtrl.content[3].phone_text]}</p>
      <p ng-if="stepsCtrl.content[3].phone_number && stepsCtrl.content[3].phone_text">
        <a href="tel:{[stepsCtrl.content[3].phone_number]}">
          {[stepsCtrl.content[3].phone_label]}
        </a>
        {[stepsCtrl.content[3].hours_of_operation]}
      </p>
    </li>
    </ol>
    <button class="modal-hidden" ng-click="stepsCtrl.closeModal()" aria-label="{[stepsCtrl.introGlobalMeta.close_modal.translatableMeta.text]}"></button>

          <li class="footer-item" ng-repeat="step in stepsCtrl.content"
              ng-class="{done: stepsCtrl.navBarPercentage >= (step.index + 1) / 4 * 99.5, active: stepsCtrl.activeStep == $index + 1}">
            <button class="footer-button" ng-click="stepsCtrl.goToStep($index + 1)">
              <span class="check">
                <svg aria-hidden="true" role="img">

        <svg aria-hidden="true" role="img">

Local Inventory Ads - Google for Retail (function(){var t=document.querySelector('html');window.dataLayer=[{event:'gfr.view',newSite:'yes',docLanguage:t.getAttribute('lang'),docRegion:(t.getAttribute('territory')||'unknown').toLowerCase(),sessionId:(new Date).getTime()+'.'+Math.random().toString(36).substring(5),hitTimestamp:(new Date).toISOString()}]})(); (function(w,d,s,l,i){w[l]=w[l]||[];w[l].push({'gtm.start': new Date().getTime(),event:'gtm.js'});var f=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0], j=d.createElement(s),dl=l!='dataLayer'?'&l='+l:'';j.async=true;j.src= 'https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtm.js?id='+i+dl;f.parentNode.insertBefore(j,f); })(window,document,'script','dataLayer','GTM-WQZWGBC'); window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || []; (function() { var experiments = createWhitelistObj(JSON.parse(getMetaContentByName('optimize_experiments').replace(/'/g, '"'))); pushExperiments(experiments); function getMetaContentByName(string) { var metaTag = document.querySelector("meta[name='" + string + "']"); return metaTag ? metaTag.getAttribute('content') : ''; } function createWhitelistObj(dictArr) { var whiteListObj = { "optimize.whitelist": {} }; dictArr.forEach(function(experiment) { whiteListObj['optimize.whitelist'][experiment.id] = experiment.signature; }); return whiteListObj; } function pushExperiments(dict) { var ownNames = Object.getOwnPropertyNames(dict["optimize.whitelist"]); if (ownNames.length > 0) { window.dataLayer.push(dict); } } }()) .async-hide { opacity: 0 !important} (function(a,s,y,n,c,h,i,d,e){s.className+=' '+y;h.start=1*new Date; h.end=i=function(){s.className=s.className.replace(RegExp(' ?'+y),'')}; (a[n]=a[n]||[]).hide=h;setTimeout(function(){i();h.end=null},c);h.timeout=c; })(window,document.documentElement,'async-hide','dataLayer',4000, {'GTM-NRTR629':true}); Consumers are already holiday shopping online. Are you ready? + Learn more for Retail Google for Retail Skip to content Overview Why Google Solutions Solutions Smart Shopping campaigns Listings Merchant Center Shopping campaigns with partners Manufacturer Center Discovery Ads Local campaigns Local Inventory Ads Product Coach Resources Resources Holiday Toolkit COVID-19 Resources Sign In Already a customer? Sign in to Merchant Center Sign in to Ads Sign in to Manufacturer Center × Get started for Retail Overview Why Google Solutions Solutions Smart Shopping campaigns Listings Merchant Center Shopping campaigns with partners Manufacturer Center Discovery Ads Local campaigns Local Inventory Ads Product Coach Resources Resources Holiday Toolkit COVID-19 Resources Close navigation drawer Already a customer? Sign in to Merchant Center Sign in to Ads Sign in to Manufacturer Center Get started Local inventory ads More and more, shoppers are using digital to find what they need in stores near them. In fact, searches for “shopping near me” have grown 3X in the past two years. Reach these consumers with local inventory ads that help nearby shoppers know what you have in stock, driving more sales to your physical store. Get started Here’s what you can do with local inventory ads Promote in-store inventory Nearly half of all shoppers globally say they confirm what they want is in stock before going to the store. When you use local inventory ads, you’re letting these prospective customers know that you have exactly what they want, right when they’re looking to buy. Today, we have over 2B offers mapped to physical store locations globally. Bring your local store online Create a virtual storefront that pairs seamlessly with your physical one by offering details like store hours, product availability, and directions. Measure performance Keep an eye on your store's performance online and off. Our robust analytics will help you understand the impact your digital ads have on in-store sales. Whether they’re searching on desktop, smartphones, or by voice, surface your products to nearby shoppers on Google. Search Assistant Images Google Search Highlight your local inventory and important business information front and center on Google Search, where hundreds of millions of people do shopping-related searches each day. Google Assistant We'll highlight in-stock products from your local feed to nearby shoppers, searching with the Google Assistant. For shoppers, finding nearby products, getting store directions, or adding items to a shopping list is just a "Hey Google" away. Google Images Shoppers are turning to Google Images to get ideas around what to buy. Now, you can also capture the attention of nearby shoppers searching for inspiration on this visual surface. STORE VISITS CONVERSION GOAL Optimize for online and in‑store conversions Whether your customers are looking for what you sell online or in the real world, you can reach them in both places. Add the store visits goal in your Smart Shopping campaigns to optimize for both online conversions and in-store purchases. Learn more Work with a certified partner to get started Get help onboarding faster with partners experienced in managing local feeds. Pointy Get your products online instantly and more customers through your door. Pointy integrates with Google to transmits sales and inventory data directly to Merchant Center. Learn more ProductsUp ProductsUp is a feed management company that specializes in feed construction, helping build and maintain your local feed. Learn more Epicor Epicor enables transactions and provides stores sales data to extrapolate inventory data to help you generate local inventory ads. Learn more View more partners Success story Big 5 Sporting Goods increases Google Search-driven foot traffic to stores by 25% Performance marketing digital agency Elite SEM partnered with Big 5’s digital marketing team to develop a retail strategy that drove a strong end-of-year holiday performance. Using local inventory ads to show real-time availability of products for last-minute shoppers, Big 5 was able to drive an increase in Google Search-driven foot traffic. “ Thanks to this trifecta partnership between Big 5, Elite, and Google, we’ve found that stores don’t make you slower, or less capable, but are actually an opportunity to make more meaningful connections by bridging the gap with digital.” — Sarah McMahon, Director of Digital Marketing & CRM at Big 5 Read more Read less Performance marketing digital agency Elite SEM partnered with Big 5’s digital marketing team to develop a retail strategy that drove a strong end-of-year holiday performance. Using local inventory ads to show real-time availability of products for last-minute shoppers, Big 5 was able to drive an increase in Google Search-driven foot traffic. “ Thanks to this trifecta partnership between Big 5, Elite, and Google, we’ve found that stores don’t make you slower, or less capable, but are actually an opportunity to make more meaningful connections by bridging the gap with digital.” - Sarah McMahon, Director of Digital Marketing & CRM at Big 5 Key stats 25% increase in Google Search-driven foot traffic to local stores year over year Success story Williams Sonoma Thanks to digital, people can shop whenever they want, wherever they want. Williams-Sonoma Inc., the iconic lifestyle retailer, needed to better understand context around where and how its customers were shopping. Local inventory ads enabled its mobile shoppers to easily find out whether the products they were searching for were in-stock at the closest store. And once in store, shoppers were more likely to extend the experience by signing up for cooking classes, getting knives sharpened, or watching a live demo on how to make the ultimate vegetable salad. “ We love this physical and digital coming together, because that's how our customers live...We want to be there online when our customer searches for information...to inspire our customers to have their home better reflect who they truly are.” — Felix Carbullido, Chief Marketing Officer, Williams Sonoma Read more Read less Thanks to digital, people can shop whenever they want, wherever they want. Williams-Sonoma Inc., the iconic lifestyle retailer, needed to better understand context around where and how its customers were shopping. Local inventory ads enabled its mobile shoppers to easily find out whether the products they were searching for were in-stock at the closest store. And once in store, shoppers were more likely to extend the experience by signing up for cooking classes, getting knives sharpened, or watching a live demo on how to make the ultimate vegetable salad. “ We love this physical and digital coming together, because that's how our customers live...We want to be there online when our customer searches for information...to inspire our customers to have their home better reflect who they truly are.” - Felix Carbullido, Chief Marketing Officer, Williams Sonoma Key stats 20% higher return on ad spend Success story SportScheck saw a 108% lift in store visits through local inventory ads SportScheck used local inventory ads to get real-time product inventory in front of mobile searchers. After rolling out local inventory ads for its in-store inventory, the brand saw an upswing in both in-store traffic and offline revenue. “ As a multi-channel retailer, it was important for us to reach customers across every channel. Local inventory ads were a great way to reach our customers with relevant product information when they went online to search.” — Rahel Götz, Team Lead for Online Performance at SportScheck Read more Read less SportScheck used local inventory ads to get real-time product inventory in front of mobile searchers. After rolling out local inventory ads for its in-store inventory, the brand saw an upswing in both in-store traffic and offline revenue. “ As a multi-channel retailer, it was important for us to reach customers across every channel. Local inventory ads were a great way to reach our customers with relevant product information when they went online to search.” - Rahel Götz, Team Lead for Online Performance at SportScheck Key stats +108% increase in in-store visits at constant store visit rate +2X offline revenue for traffic driven by local inventory ads Go back to  See  Let’s set up your local inventory ads Get started Frequently asked questions What is needed to participate in local inventory ads? To participate in local inventory ads, you’ll need a Google My Business account and local inventory data through a local products feed (which shows what you sell in stores) and a product inventory feed (which shows price and quantity of what’s available in your store). You need at least one physical store location to participate in local inventory feeds. You do not need an ecommerce website. How am I charged for local inventory ads? You pay when a user clicks on your local inventory ad, just like the way standard Shopping ads are charged. This means that you’re only charged when a user expresses interest in your product. Where can my local products show up? Local inventory ads will show on Google Search and Google Images. In addition your local products will also be eligible to show up on the “See what’s in store” knowledge panel on Google Search and Google Maps free of charge. Get started with Discovery campaigns


Promote your products across Google's feeds.




















































1. Review our best practices checklist


Set your campaign up for success with 
these tips.


























2. Collect your best assets


If you need help choosing the right visuals, review the 
Discovery creative guidelines
 or  
download our creative guide.


























3. Create your campaign


Once you're ready, 
follow these steps
 to create your campaign.


































Need more information? 
Click here.






























Additional resources to take your reach further






























See how shoppers discover your products across Google


Search, Video, Discovery, and Shopping ads help you connect with more shoppers throughout their shopping journey.



                      Watch video
                      










































Set up your Merchant Center account


Make your store and product info available to shoppers across Google. In the EEA and Switzerland, Merchant Center can be used with any Comparison Shopping Service (CSS) you work with. You can find a list of CSS partners here.


Get started




















































1. Create an account


Once you have an account open, verify important details like your business and contact information.


























2. Upload your products


Prepare your product info to submit through a feed.


























3. Show your products across Google


Opt your product data into programs, like surfaces across Google, Shopping ads, local inventory ads and Shopping Actions, to highlight your products to shoppers across Google.


































Need more information? 
Click here.






























Additional resources to take your reach further






























Merchant Center Beginner’s Guide


Learn how to get started, upload your products, and manage your data feeds.



                      Learn more
                      






























Merchant Center support


Answer any question or concern related to Merchant Center with these helpful resources.



                      Learn more
                      










































Set up a Smart Shopping campaign


Promote your products to the shoppers who are looking for what you offer on Google—whether they’re at home, on mobile, or in-store.


Get started




















































1. Verify and claim your website


Create a Merchant Center account, then claim and verify your website.


























2. Upload your products


Once you’re set up on Merchant Center, upload your product data so shoppers can see your product details, like the product image, price and availability.


























3. Create your campaign


Link your Merchant Center and Google Ads accounts. Set up conversion tracking and a remarketing list to start your first Smart Shopping campaign.


































Need more information? 
Click here.






























Additional resources to take your reach further






























Create a Smart Shopping campaign guide


Learn how to set up your Smart Shopping campaign in Google Ads.



                      Learn more
                      






























How to set up a Smart Shopping campaign


Watch this quick video to get your first campaign up and running.



                      Learn more
                      






























Merchant Center support


Get expert support as you create and manage your campaign.



                      Learn more
                      










































Set up a Search ads campaign


Get in front of customers when they’re searching for businesses like yours on Google Search and Maps.


Get started




















































1. Create your text ad


In just a few minutes, you can write a text ad that tell people what you offer.


























2. Choose your audience


Connect with potential customers by selecting relevant keywords people are searching for on Google.


























3. Set your budget


Set a daily budget, and pay per click. You’ll never pay more than your monthly max.






























Additional resources to take your reach further


Ensure that potential shoppers find your brand, consider your products, and click through to purchase.






























Search Ads support


Get help setting up your Search Ad campaigns.



                      Learn more
                      










































Set up your Shopping Actions account


Help customers shop effortlessly with you across Google at home, on mobile, or when shopping with their voice.


Get started




















































1. Create a feed


Upload your product data in Merchant Center.


























2. Setup your store


Configure your business settings: shipping, taxes, branding, returns.


























3. Publish your listings


Start selling your products directly on Google.


































Need more information? 
Click here.






























Additional resources to take your reach further






























Shopping Actions Quickstart Guide


Learn how to sell your products directly on Google with this helpful resource.



                      Learn more
                      










































Set up your local inventory ads campaign


Let nearby shoppers know what you have in stock, driving more sales in your physical store.


Get started




















































1. Set up your accounts


You need three separate accounts to run local inventory ads: Merchant Center, Google My Business Locations, and Google Ads. In Europe, Local Inventory Ads can be used with any Comparison Shopping Service (CSS) you work with. The ads will show on general search results pages and on other surfaces the CSS has opted in to. You can find a list of CSS partners here.


























2. Enable the local inventory ads program


Log in to your Merchant Center account. Enable local inventory ads in the Merchant Center Programs tab.


























3. Create, register, and submit feeds


Use Merchant Center to create and submit a local product inventory feed.


































Need more information? 
Click here.






























Additional resources to take your reach further






























Google Ads support


Get expert support as you create and manage your Ads campaigns.



                      Learn more
                      










































Set up your Manufacturer Center account


Provide up-to-date, accurate product info to Google, making it available to potential customers wherever they’re searching.


Get started




















































1. Create an account


Once you’ve determined eligibility, create a Manufacturer Account using your business details.


























2. Upload your products


Prepare your product data to submit through a feed, or work with a data partner to upload your product info.


























3. Register for the Shopping campaigns with partners beta


Let us know if you’re interested in the beta for Shopping campaigns with partners to promote your branded products with your retail partners.


































Need more information? 
Click here.






























Additional resources to take your reach further






























Quickstart setup guide


Everything you need to know to get Manufacturer Center setup, fast.



                      Learn more
                      






























Shopping campaigns with partners beta interest form


Express interest in Shopping campaigns with partners.



                      Learn more
                      










































Set up a Shopping campaign with partners


Now, brands can support their retail partners in promoting specific products and growing sales.


Get started




















































1. Register for the Shopping campaigns with partners beta


Let us know when you are ready with the form below, and we’ll reach out if you are eligible for the beta.


























2. Create a Manufacturer Center account


Shopping campaigns with partners start with Manufacturer Center. Register and create an account.


























3. Upload a product feed


Submit your product information, so we can match your products to retailers.


































Need more information? 
Click here.

Express interest in Shopping campaigns with partners.

23.pageName: Discover Street View and contribute your own imagery to Google Maps.
23.text/content:
Discover Street View and contribute your own imagery to Google Maps. new gweb.analytics.AutoTrack({profile: 'UA-61870461-1'});
Maps Street View Home Explore Businesses Enhance your listing Hire a trusted professional 360 Tools Stories Case Studies Policy Google-Contributed User-Contributed Maps Street View Home Explore Businesses Enhance your listing Hire a trusted professional 360 Tools Stories Case Studies Policy Google-Contributed User-Contributed Close the navigation drawer What is Street View? Street View, by Google Maps, is a virtual representation of our surroundings on Google Maps, consisting of millions of panoramic images. Street View’s content comes from two sources - Google and contributors. Through our collective efforts, we enable people everywhere to virtually explore the world.  {[item.title]} Where Google is collecting Street View next Discover where we’re headed next with the Street View car or the Street View trekker {[drivingCtrl.displayMonth]} / {[item]} {[key]}, ...Find out more Contribute to Street View Showcase your local community, share your surroundings, make businesses pop on Google Maps, map local roads or update Street View yourself. There are many ways to contribute, all designed to help you make a splash on Google Maps. Street View trusted program Trusted pros are experienced photographers equipped to create Street View - both at street level and indoors. Bring your surroundings to life on Google Maps by reaching out to a trusted pro. Enhance your listing Hire a trusted professional Publish connected photos With a new beta feature in the Street View app, you can create Street View with your Android smartphone Learn More Shoot and share on the go Get Street View-ready gear and publish images on the go with the Street View app . Download the Street View app .background5e775d1a1f5b8b3cbdc5a85c6430e7ce40e6d23b4935590076c78e7a { background-image: url(https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/rWT7SjD5-wRX4g_8M_otyzpY7OiD0p-wn4IDGPq41m_RV1uhbwR10BQGd16ZoB4KF4EvF7Kh1hnpVOmn2jivYler12PT3Mc_dAQSkkc); } Engage your customers, drive business Build trust and attract customers to your door — offer a high-quality virtual tour that leads them from the street to your storefront and right inside your business. Learn more When searching for businesses, consumers use mapping products 44% of the time. Ipsos study [PDF in English] On average, 41% of these place searches result in an on-site visit. Ipsos study [PDF in English] Listings with photos and a virtual tour are twice as likely to generate interest. Study details on next slide Study Details An online survey was conducted with consumers who had searched online for a restaurant or hotel within the previous 30 days (using any device). A total sample of 1201 respondents was collected between July 21st and August 2nd, 2015. Different versions of a local business listing (one for a hotel, the other for a restaurant) were created to include basic info, photos and/or a virtual tour (the same media were used to create each version). Respondents were asked to view one of the different versions for each business (in a randomized order). Each respondent viewed: 1 hotel listing + 1 restaurant listing; and 1 listing with a virtual tour + 1 listing without a virtual tour. Note: Presentation of alternate listings were randomized evenly and consistently throughout the field. After viewing each listing, respondents were instructed to rate their interest in booking a reservation. Ratings for alternate listings (with a tour versus without) were aggregated to understand the impact of virtual tours on interest in the featured business. Sign in to Merchant Center Sign in to Ads Sign in to Manufacturer Center Get started Local campaigns Local campaigns help you reach shoppers across Google to highlight your nearby stores, in-store product inventory, or special promotions. Learn more Communicate with potential customers nearby with Local campaigns Showcase your products and provide valuable information Provide shoppers with the information they need to help them decide when and how to visit your store. Let automation do the work for you Save time for what matters most to your business. Local campaigns automatically optimize your bids, creatives, and ad placements to increase visits to your store. Measure your impact in the real world Understand the in-store impact of your campaigns with reporting on store visits or calls and directions clicks. Reach millions of local shoppers across Google with one simple campaign Search Maps YouTube Business Profile Display Search Reach people who are near your location or show interest for businesses like yours. Maps Be visible when customers are nearby and show interest for locations like yours while they're searching or browsing. YouTube Reach potential local customers when they watch videos and are likely to visit your store. Business Profile Get a one-stop landing page to promote your products and special offers to customers. Display Capture local customers' attention in more places when they're browsing the web or in apps. SUCCESS STORY IKEA UK drives an 5.3 incremental return-on-ad spend IKEA, the Swedish-founded global furniture retailer, wanted to measurably drive incremental visits to its stores. The brand tested a control group against stores that used Local campaigns. The test groups yielded a significant increase in incremental sales, leading IKEA to make Local campaigns a continued part of its strategic planning. “ When Google approached us with Local campaigns, it gave us a really relevant opportunity to address the challenge of growing in-store footfall, and we were pleased to see the results from the test proved the campaign drove visits and ROI.” — Tania Douglas, Media Manager, IKEA UK Read more Read less IKEA, the Swedish-founded global furniture retailer, wanted to measurably drive incremental visits to its stores. The brand tested a control group against stores that used Local campaigns. The test groups yielded a significant increase in incremental sales, leading IKEA to make Local campaigns a continued part of its strategic planning. “ When Google approached us with Local campaigns, it gave us a really relevant opportunity to address the challenge of growing in-store footfall, and we were pleased to see the results from the test proved the campaign drove visits and ROI.” - Tania Douglas, Media Manager, IKEA UK Key stats +4.5% Incremental in-store sales 5.3 Incremental ROAS CASE STUDY Saks Fifth Avenue sees an incremental return-on-ad spend of 7.7x Saks Fifth Avenue, a luxury retailer, used Local campaigns to focus on store visits specifically during the holiday season. Using a randomized controlled geo-experiment, Saks saw its in-store sales increase and an incremental offline ROAS of 7.7x. Based on the results from the experiment, they have expanded Local campaigns to promote more of its store locations. “ We're always looking for new ways to promote and drive value from our stores, and digital is becoming increasingly critical to achieve our in-store performance goals. Local campaigns have proved very successful and we're delighted with the results!” — Ryan Butterworth, Director of Search, Saks Fifth Avenue Read more Read less Saks Fifth Avenue, a luxury retailer, used Local campaigns to focus on store visits specifically during the holiday season. Using a randomized controlled geo-experiment, Saks saw its in-store sales increase and an incremental offline ROAS of 7.7x. Based on the results from the experiment, they have expanded Local campaigns to promote more of its store locations. “ We're always looking for new ways to promote and drive value from our stores, and digital is becoming increasingly critical to achieve our in-store performance goals. Local campaigns have proved very successful and we're delighted with the results!” - Ryan Butterworth, Director of Search, Saks Fifth Avenue Key stats $460K Incremental lift in store sales 7.7x Incremental in-store return-on-ad-spend ROAS CASE STUDY Sephora achieves an incremental return-on-ad spend of 3.4x Sephora, a multinational beauty chain, knows that customers who browse and buy in-store are more valuable. With a randomized controlled geo-experiment, the brand found that Local campaigns helped increase its in-store sales. For every dollar invested, Sephora generated a positive incremental retunr-on-ad spend. “ We are excited to test and grow omni-shopping behavior through emerging digital formats. Working together with Google on a rigorous test structure, Local campaigns have proved to be a successful part of our omni toolbox.” — Aaron Katz, Sr. Mgr. Paid Search & Programmatic, Sephora Read more Read less Sephora, a multinational beauty chain, knows that customers who browse and buy in-store are more valuable. With a randomized controlled geo-experiment, the brand found that Local campaigns helped increase its in-store sales. For every dollar invested, Sephora generated a positive incremental retunr-on-ad spend. “ We are excited to test and grow omni-shopping behavior through emerging digital formats. Working together with Google on a rigorous test structure, Local campaigns have proved to be a successful part of our omni toolbox.” - Aaron Katz, Sr. Mgr. Paid Search & Programmatic, Sephora Key stats 3.4x Incremental in-store return-on-ad spend Go back to  See  Learn how to create a Local campaign Visit the Help Center Frequently asked questions What are Local campaigns? Local campaigns help you reach shoppers nearby across Google’s most popular channels. Local ads deliver broad reach and automatically find the most valuable audiences to highlight your nearby stores and increase visits to your locations. How do Local campaigns work? When you create a Local campaign, you'll just need to define the store locations you want to promote. You can set this by linking your Google My Business account or selecting affiliate locations. Local campaigns are focused on simplicity and growing your in-store business goals. You provide us with store locations, campaign budget, and ad assets. With the help of Google technology, your campaign will automatically optimize your bids, creatives, and ad placements to increase visits to your stores. s. The campaign aims to maximize your in-store value (using store visits, call clicks, or direction clicks) and promote your locations across Google properties and networks. What are some benefits of Local campaigns? Local campaigns are the first-ever Google Ads campaign type that are specifically designed to optimize for store visits. It is a fully automated solution from end-to-end to optimize your bids, creatives, and ad placements to increase visits to your stores. Local campaigns run across Google’s major properties, and shows your ads across Search, Display, Maps, Business Profile,and YouTube. They also provide access to new ad inventory such as Maps promoted pins and local results on Search. Follow us About Google for Retail Overview Why Google? Frequently Asked Questions




Who is Earth Studio for?


Earth Studio is a web-based animation tool for Google Earth imagery. Google Earth has a massive store of satellite and aerial (3D) imagery from large-scale geological features to individual city buildings. Earth Studio is the easiest way to leverage this imagery for still and animated content.






How is Earth Studio different from Google Earth?


Earth Studio and Google Earth serve different purposes. Google Earth enables you to travel and learn about the world through a virtual globe. You can view satellite imagery, maps, terrain, 3D buildings and much more. Earth Studio, on the other hand, is a tool for animating geospatial information to create still and video content. They both share the same imagery dataset and use the same 3D rendering engine but have different features. Read more about Earth Studio 
here
.






How do I get access?


Earth Studio requires a Google account and currently works in Google Chrome only. To request access, please fill out the form 
here
. You will receive an email whether or not you are accepted.






How much does Earth Studio cost?


Earth Studio is free to use for news, research, education, and nonprofit use.






Can I use Earth Studio for commercial applications?


We currently do not offer a license to use Google Earth imagery for commercial applications. This includes using Earth Studio content without attribution.






What terms apply to my use of Earth Studio?


We ask that you follow our 
Google Maps/Google Earth Additional Terms of Service
, and that all content created and distributed follows our 
attribution guidelines
, which include the requirement that ‘Google Earth’ and third-party imagery providers (if applicable) shown on screen for the duration of said content.






What types of content can I use Earth Studio for?


As long as content created from Earth Studio is properly attributed, it can be used for any application such as research, education, film and nonprofit use. For more information and other uses, please review our 
permission guidelines
.






Who owns the content I create in Earth Studio?


You keep ownership of any intellectual property rights that you hold in content created using Earth Studio. Google, its licensors, or users own content that can be viewed and used via Earth Studio, subject to the 
Google Maps/Google Earth Additional Terms of Service
. For more information, please refer to our 
permission guidelines
.






Where does the imagery come from?


Google Earth imagery encompasses information that is available from a broad range of providers, including public, government, and commercial sources. The same information is generally available to anyone who licenses or purchases it from these sources.






Why is Earth Studio Chrome-only?


Earth and Earth Studio both run on a web technology called WebAssembly. This allows Google Earth to 
work on most broswers today
. However, Earth Studio still relies on a couple of Chrome-only APIs for rendering animations. We are continuously investigating alternative rendering methods that could work in other browsers.






Why don't my KMLs work properly in Earth Studio?


Most moderately-sized KML files and simple features should work in Earth Studio. While we work to support more advanced features you can keep using the classic desktop Google Earth app. 
Learn more
.






What's the best way to get support?


Learn more about how to use Earth Studio and its features in our 
documentation
, which contains helpful tutorials and best practices. You can also provide feedback directly from the tool under Help > Give Feedback.
